An '''election''' for the office of [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] was held by the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]]<ref name="Characters">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[28 BBY/Legends|28 BBY]] (7:10:5 [[Great ReSynchronization|GrS]]). The sitting Chancellor, [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], was re-elected for his second four-year term. The Senate later [[Emergency Powers Act/Legends|modified]] the [[Galactic Constitution/Legends|Galactic Constitution]] in [[24 BBY/Legends|24 BBY]],<ref name="Holonet" /> to extend Palpatine's time in office beyond the traditional eight-year term limit.<ref name="Characters" />

==Behind the scenes==
Palpatine's reelection as Supreme Chancellor was first mentioned in the [[2002]] sourcebook ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'', written by [[Daniel Wallace]].<ref name="Characters" />

